from IPython.display import HTML
HTML('''<script>
code_show=true;
function code_toggle(){
if (code_show){
$('div.input').hide();
document.getElementById('btn_toggle').value="Show Code";
}else {
$('div.input').show();
document.getElementById('btn_toggle').value="Hide Code";
}
code_show=!code_show
}
$(document).ready(code_toggle);
</script>
<style>
.output_png {
    display: table-cell;
    text-align: center;
    vertical-align: middle;
</style>
<form action="javascript:code_toggle()">
<input style="float:right" type="submit" id="btn_toggle">

''')

13. Distplot
¶

This function combines the matplotlib hist function (with automatic calculation of a good default bin size) with the seaborn kdeplot() and rugplot() functions. It can also fit scipy.stats distributions and plot the estimated PDF over the data.

In [27]:
x=np.random.randn(100)
sns.distplot(x);

15. Rugplot
¶

Plot marginal distributions by drawing ticks along the x and y axes.

This function is intended to complement other plots by showing the location of individual observations in an unobstrusive way.

In [29]:
sns.kdeplot(data=tips.total_bill);
sns.rugplot(a=tips.total_bill);

Multiple plots in same graph
¶

In [2]:
basket=[]
apple=("Apple," * random.randint(1,100)).split(",")
grapes=("Grape," * random.randint(1,100)).split(",")
orange=("Orange," * random.randint(1,100)).split(",")
basket.extend(apple)
basket.extend(grapes)
basket.extend(orange)
basket=pd.Series(data=basket,name="Item")
basket.drop(basket[basket.values==""].index,inplace=True)
basket_value_cnt=basket.value_counts()
cum_percent=basket_value_cnt.cumsum()/basket_value_cnt.sum()*100
In [6]:
sns.reset_defaults()
In [7]:
fig,ax=plt.subplots(figsize=(20,10))
ax.bar(basket_value_cnt.index,basket_value_cnt.values,color='lightblue');

ax2=ax.twinx()
ax2.plot(cum_percent.index,cum_percent,color='red',marker='D',ms=5)
ax2.yaxis.set_major_formatter(PercentFormatter())

ax.tick_params(axis='y', colors='blue')
ax2.tick_params(axis='y',colors='red')
plt.show()
